article.headline: Northern Arizona 100, Johnson and Wales (Den) 52
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Ruben Boykin Jr. had 20 points and 13 rebounds, helping Northern Arizona beat Johnson & Wales 100-52 on Saturday. Will Hensley added 14 points for the Lumberjacks (8-6), Steve Sir had 12 and Kelly Golob scored 11. Ryuji Brumley and Eric Daniels scored 17 points each for Johnson & Wales (0-19). The game was close for only a few minutes. Golob had two of his four 3-pointers for an early 8-0 lead. Brumley and Daniels answered with a 3-pointer apiece to cut the deficit to 8-6 just 2:41 into the game, but Tyrone Bazy started a 15-0 with a 3-pointer, and the Lumberjacks ran away to a 23-6 lead less than halfway through the first half.
